Guangxi university student suspended study and entrepreneurship may be up to 5 years - Xinhua.
Xinhua News Agency, Nanning, May 19th: Recently, the Education Bureau of Guangxi Autonomous Region has announced that all universities in Guangxi will implement flexible education systems that loosen the maximum limit for student suspensions, extending the enforced leave of absence for entrepreneurship from the original rule based system to two to five years, and viewing the time of suspension for entrepreneurship as practical education time.
In order to promote the ability of college students to start their own businesses and be innovative, departments such as Education and Human Resources of Guangxi have worked together to build an entrepreneurship platform, and have established more college student practical teaching bases, University Science and Technology Parks, College Student Entrepreneurship Parks, Entrepreneurship Incubators, etc., to provide an external guarantee for college student entrepreneurship.
By the requirements, by 2020, each university's innovation and business practice base area should be over 3,000 square meters for undergraduate universities and over 2,000 square meters for higher vocational universities.
The government encourages universities to set up innovative and entrepreneurial credits, giving priority to students who demonstrate excellence in innovative and entrepreneurial practice when transferring majors.
High school teachers should be attached to industry enterprises for at least two months every two years in order to enhance the awareness and ability of teachers in innovative and entrepreneurial education.
The Autonomous Region Education Department requires all universities in Guangxi to implement the University Student Innovation and Entrepreneurship Training Program, striving to ensure that every university student participates in an innovation and entrepreneurship training program during schooling periods.
High schools should actively organize students to participate in various innovation and entrepreneurship competitions at all levels, and provide financial support.
